
{{> header}}
<title>ATS Portal</title>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="container">
        {{> menu}}
        <h1>ATS Portal</h1>
        <p>This will be a "control panel" to access the various elements of the ATS program.
        </p>
        <h2>User types</h2>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col">
                <strong>Vex Securities</strong><br>Registed Principals and Representatives of Vex Securities LLC
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <strong>Account Holders/Members</strong><br>Accredited investors who have access to the ATS as members.
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <strong>Audit</strong><br>Read Only. Auditors, regulators and Vex Securities software engineers will be able to view and query.
            </div>
        </div>
        <h2>Database Tables</h2>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col">
                <strong>BD Account Holder Data</strong><br>Member required data for maintaining an account with Vex Securities and membership of the ATS. This will also include pending accounts and records of representative proposals and principal reviews.
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <strong>Approved Securities</strong><br>The list of Securities that can be traded on the ATS.
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <strong>Central Limit Order Book</strong><br>A list of all open orders for all approved securities, in price then time priority. All new orders will be executed against or added to the order book depending on the particulars of the order.
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <strong>Transaction Record</strong><br>All matched orders will be recorded here and sent to the Transfer Agent for settlement.
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <strong>Queries</strong><br>All queries and any responses will be recorded here with timestamps.
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <strong>Change Log</strong><br>All changes to the overall database along with the identity of the participant responsible for the change shall be located here for audit purposes.
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
{{> footer}}